Date: 0/0/1981
Source: Loughnan Glossary
Author: LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page: 57
Edition:
Quote: old man: a kind of extra-superlative adverbial or adjectival phrase, often used to describe something particularly pestilential or annoying ( eg old-man couch grass or a real old-man nor'wester but it can also indicate something of great age (an old man totara).
